From 67941bd99579f8ea6ca251192fdbd724fe6fb8dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rouven Czerwinski <r.czerwinski@pengutronix.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Nov 2021 17:15:01 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 17/25] tc358746: return -ENOTCONN if there is no link

In case the link to the sensor has not been set up yet, we can't request
hblank and pixelclock from the sensor. Return -ENOTCONN to indicate that
a sensor needs to be connected to set the format.

Signed-off-by: Rouven Czerwinski <r.czerwinski@pengutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: ian.dannapel <ian.dannapel@iris-sensing.com>
---
 drivers/media/i2c/tc358746.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/tc358746.c b/drivers/media/i2c/tc358746.c
index 351a079cc7ed..2d9d9ac9aba6 100644
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/tc358746.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/tc358746.c
@@ -1214,6 +1214,10 @@ static int tc358746_set_fmt(struct v4l2_subdev *sd,
 	unsigned int new_freq, cur_freq = v4l2_ctrl_g_ctrl(state->link_freq);
 	u16 vb_fifo;
 
+	/* link has not been set up, we can't retrieve ctrls from the sensor */
+	if (!state->sensor_pclk_ctrl || !state->sensor_hblank_ctrl)
+		return -ENOTCONN;
+
 	if (pad->flags == MEDIA_PAD_FL_SOURCE)
 		return tc358746_get_fmt(sd, cfg, format);
 
-- 
2.25.1

